issue.body:
Bumps the development-minor-patch group with 3 updates: [knip](https://github.com/webpro-nl/knip/tree/HEAD/packages/knip), [puppeteer](https://github.com/puppeteer/puppeteer) and [@mdn/browser-compat-data](https://github.com/mdn/browser-compat-data). Updates `knip` from 5.54.1 to 5.55.1
Release notes

Sourced from knip's releases.

  • Update Node.js versions in CI (09a158b4fa6f9e0e7d72b62f99120d7d36be8714)

performed_via_github_app.name: changeset-bot
performed_via_github_app.description: This bot will comment on PRs saying that either a user might need to add a changeset(note that PRs changing things like documentation generally don't need a changeset)or say that the PR is good and already has a changeset. Sometimes, a contributor won't add a changeset to a PR but you might want to merge in the PR without having to wait on them to add it. To address this, this bot adds a link with the filename pre-filled to add a changeset so all you have to do is write the changeset and click commit. When writing the changeset, it should look something like this with the packages that are being released in the YAML front matter with associated semver bump types and the summary of the changes in markdown. ```markdown --- '@changesets/cli': major '@changesets/read': minor --- A very helpful description of the changes ```

issue.title: Fix hardcoded credentials vulnerability (CWE-798)
issue.body:
# Fix hardcoded credentials vulnerability (CWE-798)

This PR addresses the hardcoded credentials vulnerability identified by CodeQL analysis. The changes replace hardcoded secrets with environment variables and ensure proper fallback mechanisms for development environments.

## Changes made:
- Updated JWT public/private key fallbacks to use environment variables
- Added environment variables for test credentials (TEST_JWT_SECRET, TEST_HMAC_SECRET)
- Updated user credentials to use environment variables instead of hardcoded values
- Improved fallback mechanisms for development environments
- Updated .env.example with new environment variables
- Added verification script to test credential loading

## Security improvements:
- Removed hardcoded JWT secrets from the codebase
- Removed hardcoded HMAC secrets from test files
- Implemented secure fallbacks for test environments
- Added proper documentation for required environment variables

Link to Devin run: https://app.devin.ai/sessions/04625485a3fe4fc18f12f1e69e400bf5
Requested by: brianlai4242@gmail.com

pull_request.title: Feat/home
pull_request.body:
Desenvolvimento da Home do cliente e do entregador

Esta solicitação de pull apresenta melhorias na interface do usuário para a DeliveryHomeScreen e HomeScreen, com foco na melhoria do layout, do posicionamento dos elementos-chave e consumo de API. As alterações visam aprimorar a hierarquia visual, a usabilidade e a experiência geral do usuário, refinando o design da barra de status e o alinhamento dos elementos. Essas atualizações complementam a base de código existente, mantendo a funcionalidade.

UI Layout Improvements:

  • Relocated the back button from a standalone Positioned widget to be integrated within the gray status bar (DecoratedBox) at the top of the DeliveryHomeScreen, improving visual cohesion and accessibility. The button is now positioned on the left side using mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.spaceBetween.
  • Adjusted the gray status bar's size in the DeliveryHomeScreen by setting a fixed width (width: 300) and height (height: 40), making it more compact and visually balanced compared to its previous full-width design.
  • Centralized the "Disponível" status and notification icon within the gray status bar of the DeliveryHomeScreen by applying MainAxisAlignment.center to a nested Row, ensuring better alignment and a polished appearance while keeping the back button on the left.
  • [Placeholder] Added or updated layout improvements for the HomeScreen (please provide specific changes if applicable).

API Consumption:

  • [Placeholder] Integrated or updated API consumption logic for the DeliveryHomeScreen and/or HomeScreen (please provide specific API-related changes if applicable).

Miscellaneous Fixes:

  • Reduced padding (EdgeInsets.symmetric(horizontal: 8, vertical: 4)) and adjusted icon sizes (size: 20) within the gray status bar of the DeliveryHomeScreen to fit the new compact design, ensuring all elements are properly displayed without overflow.
  • Maintained the modal's drag functionality and overall screen behavior (e.g., minimizing on tap outside) in the DeliveryHomeScreen to prevent regressions in existing features.

Impact:

  • Positive: Improves the visual hierarchy and usability of the DeliveryHomeScreen (and potentially HomeScreen) by providing a more organized and compact status bar layout. Enhances user experience with a more intuitive back button placement and centralized status information.
  • Negative: No significant negative impact expected. The changes are localized to the UI layout and do not affect core functionality or other screens.
  • Risk: Minimal risk, as the modal and map functionalities in the DeliveryHomeScreen have been tested to ensure no regressions. However, screen size variations (e.g., smaller devices) should be verified to ensure proper rendering.

Tests:

  • Verified that the back button correctly navigates to the previous screen when tapped in the DeliveryHomeScreen.
  • Confirmed that the "Disponível" status and notification icon are centrally aligned within the gray status bar of the DeliveryHomeScreen.
  • Tested the modal's drag behavior (minimize on tap outside, expand on drag up) to ensure it works as expected in the DeliveryHomeScreen.
  • Checked the layout on different screen sizes to ensure the adjusted status bar fits well in the DeliveryHomeScreen.
  • [Placeholder] Tested layout and functionality updates for the HomeScreen (please provide specific tests if applicable).

Checklist:

  • [x] Código revisado e testado localmente.
  • [x] Não há erros de compilação ou comportamento inesperado.
  • [x] Documentação atualizada (se aplicável).

pull_request.title: Add CompletableFuture Support for Callback-based Async RPC
pull_request.body:
### Motivation:

[Issue #945](https://github.com/sofastack/sofa-rpc/issues/945)
SOFA-rpc uses a callback-based asynchronous response model and lacks the ability to to handle async responses with
CompletableFuture introduced in Java8. Developers need to manually wrap the callback to integrate with chain operations,
which is inconvenient.
[Pull #1323](https://github.com/sofastack/sofa-rpc/pull/1323)
The issue had been addressed before. But letting ResponseFuture inherit CompletionStage is too intrusive and could introduce compatibility issues across the codebase.

### Modification:

- Introduces new bridge class SofaCallbackCompletableFuture
  - Integrates with RpcInvokeContext 
  - Compatible with callback mechanism with support of chain operations
- Integration test with real RPC

### Result:

- Avoided modifications to ResponseFuture
- Can now use CompletableFuture API directly in callbacks

## Usage Example
```java
// Create future instance first
SofaCompletableResponseFuture<String> future = SofaCompletableResponseFuture.create();

// Make RPC call
service.sayHello("test", 22);

// Chain process
String result = future
    .thenApply(res -> res + " (process1)")
    .thenApply(res -> res + " (process2)")
    .get(5, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
```

This is my first PR . I'm happy to make any changes as needed—thanks!

<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->

## Summary by CodeRabbit

- **New Features**
  - Introduced a new asynchronous future class for enhanced non-blocking RPC response handling.
- **Tests**
  - Added comprehensive integration tests to validate asynchronous service calls, exception propagation, timeouts, cancellations, and callback chaining.

<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->
